Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.00,0:01:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Japan-US trade frictions
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.36,0:01:54.61,top,,0,0,0,,Welcome Ms. Matsumoto Sawako
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.47,0:01:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Is she really coming by that plane?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.03,0:02:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe I got the wrong flight number... \NOr she simply passed by.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.59,0:02:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,"Taihei Shoji" sent you to greet me?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.28,0:02:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Matsumoto Sawako.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.18,0:02:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Taihei really is acquiring a brilliant employee!\NI don't get to greet a Harvard graduate every day!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.35,0:02:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,To go studying abroad one needs a lot of wits and guts.\NSeeing you here with me is almost like an illusion!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.35,0:02:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only that, \Nyou got a master's with summa cum laude!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.36,0:02:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that you could get the first hand American idea of automobiles is just unbelievable!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.36,0:02:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't express, how much I admire you!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.33,0:02:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,This traffic jam is strange... \NIt's not even rush hour yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.33,0:02:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,This happens every time I find a passenger!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.52,0:02:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I see... Well, we still have a little time.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.48,0:03:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Ms. Yukie, why don't we take a walk? \NLet us get off here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.60,0:03:14.37,top,,0,0,0,,October 1980\NUSA, Detroit, Michigan
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.48,0:03:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,How many cars do you think\NAmerica has produced this year?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.89,0:03:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Last year, due to a sudden surge in demand, \Nit was a million and 480 thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.14,0:03:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Japan then became the world's number one car manufacturer. The United States remain number two to this day.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.21,0:03:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We are boycotting the Japs!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.92,0:03:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't need their scrap!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.36,0:03:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,If our union is idle, we will act ourselves!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.95,0:03:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We've had enough of chinks! \NGive us back our job!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.55,0:03:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a Japanese one!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.76,0:03:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll make them pay!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.51,0:03:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's get the Jap's car destroyed!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.50,0:03:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Eat this!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.84,0:03:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Burn to the ground!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.33,0:04:10.33,top,,0,0,0,,Central Automobile Association Chairman, Hoffman
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.47,0:04:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's me. I want to make a call to Washington.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.83,0:04:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Hoffman must be one hell of a happy about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.75,0:04:22.05,top,,0,0,0,,Showa Automobile Company President
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.75,0:04:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Under such a great pressure, \NWashington might demand actions from us as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.05,0:04:27.05,top,,0,0,0,,Showa Automobile Company CEO
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.05,0:04:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,In turn, the Japanese government won't hesitate \Nto comply with their American colleagues.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.05,0:04:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, our government \Nwill accept all of the restrictions,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.66,0:04:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's the only way to protect themselves from all the political and legal blame.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.49,0:04:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Those parasites have no idea that once Japanese cars stop getting to the market, our economy will collapse.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.63,0:04:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,This will only lead to the increase of price.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.78,0:04:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is, indeed, exactly what they are aiming for. \NIf the price rises, the number of Japanese cars sold will fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.31,0:04:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, "Central" will be the only one to benefit from the trade turnover decrease.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.41,0:04:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to believe those frictions are temporary.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.50,0:05:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people make fortunes playing money games like this one. They'd do anything for profit except improving their means of production.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.52,0:05:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,While we reduced the number of workers \Nto one person per vehicle,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.65,0:05:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,even applying all the rationalization means they know, \Nthey can't assemble a car with less than three persons involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.95,0:05:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm afraid, \Nthis industrial action is bigger than the previous ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.40,0:05:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Are they planning to ban imports \Nto increase their own cars' sales?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.48,0:05:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed. Workers' protests are just a public excuse.\NAnd they won't leave the streets until their wish is granted.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.45,0:05:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But don't they understand that a market rivalry is wholesome for product's cost and quality?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.06,0:05:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It already forced our Hayate colleagues to relocate their assembly lines this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.17,0:05:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Although it didn't affect us so far...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.00,0:05:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, we should foresee this shift \Nand face it prepared, is that what you're trying to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.96,0:05:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll have to do it, sooner or later.\NTo save our money, actions have to be taken right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.68,0:05:58.60,top,,0,0,0,,Main Business Headquarters
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.68,0:05:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Export self-restrictions have been placed.\NThe government didn't even try to resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.60,0:06:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess we won't see a planned 1 680 000 cars next year... \NWell, such turn of events is to be expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.55,0:06:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I'll hand it over \Nto the president and see what he says.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.74,0:06:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.07,0:06:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,President! The telex just came, just as you said...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.31,0:06:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Self-restrictions placement? No need. Hayate \Nautomobile company president just called me to discuss it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.50,0:06:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.75,0:06:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Ms. Matsumoto, Hayate's are grateful for your advise to move production lines in advance.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.97,0:06:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,No... It's not a big deal, \Nanyone could do the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.65,0:06:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We appreciate your modesty, but thanks to your forethought, Hayate are fully prepared for the following crisis.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.46,0:06:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Your advice to move production lines has played a big role. \NWe cannot ignore such foresight.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.77,0:06:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Or, at the very least, when the Showa Company needs it, \Nwe should give this 23-year-old talent a chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.75,0:06:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's just a girl \Nwho graduated from Harvard Business School.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.15,0:06:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need a lot of talent \Nto just go studying abroad!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.55,0:06:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Manager, just because she's a woman, \Nyou mistreat her?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.91,0:06:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Ms. Yukie...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.15,0:07:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, I mentioned it \Nbecause Showa carmaker recently contacted us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.66,0:07:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Showa you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.88,0:07:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Your work for Hayate impressed them. They want to hear a lecture about production relocation from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.92,0:07:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So Showa are also seriously considering relocating their production lines back here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.40,0:07:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't say if they're serious yet. Mikawa and Matsumoto, wouldn't you mind to meet their president on this Saturday's evening?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.18,0:07:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, I have to refuse. \NOn Saturday I'm leaving for a private consultation in Kyoto.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.94,0:07:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, you... This company is virtually a market monopolist. Will you give up the chance to work with "Showa"!?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.94,0:07:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,All the details of the Hayate's production relocation process are recorded here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.70,0:07:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,This notebook will be more than enough \Nto solve any problem they might encounter.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.45,0:07:42.43,top,,0,0,0,,Kyoto
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.43,0:07:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I was anticipating these events long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.71,0:07:50.72,top,,0,0,0,,Residence of Sawako's benefactor, Kyoto University of Economics and Sociology professor, Funaoka Muneichiro
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.71,0:07:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Once the restrictions are placed, the price of Japanese cars will rise to an average of $2,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.72,0:07:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Without export, the overproduction \Nwill supply the entire prefecture with cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.04,0:07:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we'll even have some left for change.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.97,0:08:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,In its turn, the American cars price rise \Nwill deplete buyers pockets.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.40,0:08:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result, \Nordinary Americans will be the only victims, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.23,0:08:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Glad you figured it out yourself. \NIt's all leading us to forming a Japan-US monopoly cartel.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.90,0:08:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,However, I think we still have time before that happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.49,0:08:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,What makes you think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.99,0:08:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The currency market...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.49,0:08:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,American foreign trade after 1970 became financially scarce.
