Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.50,0:08:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You can only imagine how irreparable \Ninternal budget hole has become.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.19,0:08:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And to somehow fill it, the government plunged into a bunch of external public debts.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.65,0:08:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But as you well know \Nneither external nor public debts have been of any help.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.95,0:08:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.49,0:08:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, now to pay off all of America's external debts,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.52,0:08:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the dollar, which has become the world's currency, has to be printed in the unthinkable amount.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.13,0:08:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It will be an infinite stream of dollars. \NNeedless to say, how the dollar's exchange rate will drop then.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.02,0:08:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Its price will fluctuate like the sea during a storm.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.48,0:08:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The yen will rise when dollar gets cheaper?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.57,0:08:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly. Each dollar, which now worth more than 200 yen, will then cost 170 yen, if not less.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.18,0:08:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And chances are the worst is yet to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.37,0:09:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But if things go that way, won't maintenance of production lines in America will become even more profitable for Japan?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.31,0:09:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You got it right away. \NAnd then we'll only have one problem left...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.88,0:09:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,...Local working conditions deterioration?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.09,0:09:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If that happens, \Nour subcontractors will suffer the greatest damage.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.61,0:09:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,If you are looking for Showa subcontractors, \Nthis should fulfill your interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.85,0:09:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You are...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.88,0:09:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Archive manager, Yuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.48,0:09:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Apologies... You weren't on the spot, \Nso I helped myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.80,0:09:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I work in Main Business Headquarters...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.90,0:09:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Ms. Matsumoto Sawako, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.91,0:09:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.13,0:09:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This lively girl has already introduced you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.40,0:09:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Ms. Yukie...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.16,0:09:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I always come here for dinner, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.17,0:09:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,My...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.19,0:09:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,In the late seventies, I was amongst the many who got exposed to the unpleasant experience of selling color TVs and other junk.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.40,0:09:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And I know firsthand \Nwhat a big deal car production relocation is.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.66,0:09:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.65,0:10:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, if that would help, I can get you color TV production relocation recordings.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.93,0:10:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That would make a great help!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.68,0:10:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, where was it...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.44,0:10:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, Ms. Yukie, this Mr. Yuki, the librarian. \NWhat kind of person he is?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.43,0:10:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Main candidate for the head of the department and big careerist. But sometimes he looks like something is bothering him...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.20,0:10:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Like he is coping with responsibility for something from the past. I often see him standing by the window, deep in thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.17,0:10:34.44,top,,0,0,0,,{\q2\blur1\fs14\bord0\b1\fscx95\fscy100\t(3500,6500,\c&HFFFAFF&)\pos(221.889,366)}\h                         With Pictures                                       \h\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N{\fs20}\h                                 An Introduction to Japanese Economy
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.05,0:10:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Two years after the first export self-restrictions \NJapanese cars became more expensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.97,0:10:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The American auto industry increased the prices as well.\NCentral Association has just started handling with this crisis.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.45,0:10:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,However, America has suffered financial reforms, \Nwhich strengthened the yen further.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.98,0:10:52.96,top,,0,0,0,,Meeting of the Central Automobile Association shareholders
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.69,0:10:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The price for Japanese cars \Nis about to rise once more.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.98,0:10:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I am happy to announce that we defeated injustice without resorting to the price increase.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.07,0:11:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfair working hours, government disloyalty to workers, and other ineffective Japanese means of competition
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.48,0:11:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,have been officially denounced internationally. \NJapan was obliged to radically change its foreign policy course.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.25,0:11:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But most of all, I am proud that the dollar-yen exchange rate has remained at a reasonable level.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.75,0:11:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The Japanese cars' competitiveness reduced drastically, \Nand as a manufacturer I hope too,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.05,0:11:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that soon enough our companies will start relocating their production lines to Japan themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.03,0:11:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,If we call ourselves Americans, \Nwe have no right to lose in that industry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.25,0:11:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So I, as the Central Automobile Association president,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.12,0:11:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,promise you to start exporting our cars to Japan in a matter of the next few years!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.61,0:11:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We've had enough of their jokes!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.09,0:11:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as they accept all the petty American demands, we only become poorer!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.09,0:11:44.83,top,,0,0,0,,Showa Automobile Company Workers Union Chairman, \NKatsutoshi Sato
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.14,0:11:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's you and I, ordinary workers, \Nwho suffer from this more than any of them!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.94,0:11:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,For the sake of preserving our union, \Nwe must confront them!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.87,0:11:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Give 'em hell!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.37,0:11:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Have no doubt that we are the main victims of those trade difficulties! That's right, comrades!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.72,0:12:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,At a working meeting this morning it was decided that we are not moving production lines away from America, in spite of expenses.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.25,0:12:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, we ask you, \NGoyo and Taihei representatives,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.25,0:12:11.27,top,,0,0,0,,Goyo Manufacturing and Business Committee \NPresident Gondo                         Kunio Tsugawa
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.17,0:12:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to discuss during this meeting, \Nhow our local factories will work from now on.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.92,0:12:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to come to a compromise solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.73,0:12:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I get it you are being easily swayed, since you now even employ girls fresh from school.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.28,0:12:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Tsugawa, please watch your mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.66,0:12:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.31,0:12:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Toda, don't you think you really are being too soft?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.46,0:12:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'd say it's you who are being too soft.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.76,0:12:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I ask just one question regarding the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.36,0:12:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.38,0:12:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Labor unions, \Nhave you already figured how to deal with them?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.30,0:12:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That issue should be out of your concern, \Nwe have our own ways to negotiate with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.55,0:12:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,This scoundrel Gondo regularly gets swayed by shady specialists himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.52,0:12:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,This time I was even close to punching his nose...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.60,0:12:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,President, please let me figure this out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.50,0:13:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,After the Hayate issue, I came up with this secret strategy of production expansion, which they won't be able to reject.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.51,0:13:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I hope this is something worthy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.51,0:13:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I had an idea \Nthat we might just inherit local factories on site.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.53,0:13:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll write a report due to this evening \Nso you'll see it yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.58,0:13:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds good. Ms. Matsumoto, \Ndo you happen to have any alternatives?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.89,0:13:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm convinced that research among subcontractors \Nhas to be conducted.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.38,0:13:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Subcontractors?{\i0} \NWhat is it out there that I can't tell you right away?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.30,0:13:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have nothing else to do besides that, \Nyou'd better come and help me with my idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.58,0:13:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry for returning your own words, \Nbut the Goyo Committee, most likely,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.30,0:13:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,has already taken the first steps towards new potential sites.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.54,0:13:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But if we show the ability to look from a different angle now, \Nin the long term, Showa will prefer to appeal to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.97,0:13:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, this has to be done at any rate.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.78,0:13:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Subcontractors and parts manufacturers are, indeed, \Nan important part of this play...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.56,0:13:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I got it. As soon as we get back, \Nyou'll both make a report for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.04,0:13:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.54,0:13:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Your talents will apply perfectly. \NChoose the method yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.66,0:13:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Just... refrain from breaking people's backs. \NThis time, be careful, in every way.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.33,0:14:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,No need to teach me... Mr. Tsugawa, I will never let down the most precious of my clients.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.30,0:14:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Sato has only his union behind him, \Nbut his ambitions are already rather councilor's.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.49,0:14:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,One good scandal should be enough \Nto bring him back to earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.63,0:14:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Seems like this guy really pissed you off...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.06,0:14:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Right... Once "Showa" sees how fervently we sort everything out, \Nthey won't even remember what "Taihei" is.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.78,0:14:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Since the self-restrictions were placed, \Nthe production has almost stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.74,0:14:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And it seems, that soon it'll stop completely.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.02,0:14:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But the situation might improve too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.06,0:14:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to say anything indecent about Showa company, to which I am indebted...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.89,0:14:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I always looked forward to meeting with them before.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.64,0:14:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, what's your opinion on Showa's decision to continue assembling vehicles in America without lines relocation?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.01,0:14:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you say?\NNow's not the time for jokes!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.84,0:14:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm told the Showa's union is unanimously against this decision. Am I being deceived?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.10,0:14:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,No... At the moment, \Nthat is the current state of affairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.10,0:15:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then, don't you get that without access to parts from Japan, your assembly lines out there are useless?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.86,0:15:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It is thanks to the individual subcontractors like us, \NJapanese cars are so popular and cheap!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.36,0:15:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But the way you want it done, \Nnewly produced parts won't be able to leave Japan!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.37,0:15:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,There are certain loopholes...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.03,0:15:17.87,Default,,0,0,0,,According to current restrictions, \Nif at least 50% of the parts are manufactured locally,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.87,0:15:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the vehicle is not considered imported \Nand parts are not being banned.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.83,0:15:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But even so... Half of the companies will be unwanted. \NWhat should we produce then?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.13,0:15:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Do I... Have to find money \Nto relocate my whole factory now?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.60,0:15:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Ms. Matsumoto, \Nfor small subcontractors like us, this is vital!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.89,0:15:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't Taihei, by any chance, \Nfind some new work for us before it's too late?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.61,0:15:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,A new work for car parts manufacturers...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.86,0:15:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Expropriating poorly managed local manufacturers?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.95,0:15:53.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Quite a bold plan, I must say.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.99,0:15:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Mikawa, you understand that this course calls for some sharp practice, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.20,0:16:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That's exactly why I chose it. \NShowa is all about bold actions!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.46,0:16:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And what makes it especially good - \Nit is the cheapest of all!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.71,0:16:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But at the same time, to get this plan going, huge investments are needed at first.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.21,0:16:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Such investments are not a big deal for Showa! Why won't you let me handle this personally?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.34,0:16:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't make an omelet without breaking eggs.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.68,0:16:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You are eager to act, just as always. \NAlright, be ready for some private property retrieval US trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.52,0:16:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.56,0:16:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Ms. Matsumoto, you have something to offer too?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.98,0:16:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. My proposal is also \Nabout expanding Showa's manufacture in America.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.09,0:16:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And instead of buying, with its own manufactures, the company could obtain parts with other ways, described in this research.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.23,0:16:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what conclusion did you come to?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.75,0:16:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Color TVs were the subject \Nof similar trade frictions a few years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.39,0:16:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Japanese manufacturers then also relocated their production and found themselves at a crossroad.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.25,0:16:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result, to this day, \Ncolor TV export to America remains very low.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.26,0:16:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of the companies have expanded their production \Nby absorbing parts manufacturers.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.58,0:17:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, it seems, that time the parts subcontractors located here didn't have any problems surviving.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.77,0:17:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And even when America \Nhas opened its own TV production line,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.44,0:17:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,we could quickly convert our lines \Nto VTR production and save a lot of effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.50,0:17:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,VTRs came in like a sort of pinch hitters to replace the demanded player at the time of need.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.01,0:17:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,But no pinch hitter of that kind might appear in the automobile industry, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.99,0:17:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly. TVs, unlike automobiles, do not consist of such an off scale number of parts.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.75,0:17:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The number of subcontractors was also fewer, so this time parts manufacturers won't make it out so easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.11,0:17:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You were persuading Hayate \Nto relocate their production to the homeland.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.97,0:17:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But for Showa you do the opposite. \NThis is suspicious...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.76,0:17:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Hayate had much fewer production facilities, the relocation of which didn't cause that much trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.50,0:17:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I got it. You say we should stick to the current course \Nto break through the sanctions?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.02,0:17:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. With the help of Ms. Yukie \Nand the archive manager, Mr. Yuki, if you want me to,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.31,0:17:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I may come up with a new joint business plan for the company and its subcontractors.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.53,0:17:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand. If you can, please do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.75,0:17:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.41,0:18:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So we are saving the local small businesses now? \NMakes sense. These guys are always the most vulnerable.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.42,0:18:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But don't you think that secretly deciding the fate of someone else's company is a bit overconfident?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.93,0:18:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, we have no idea \Nhow the people working there feel...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.93,0:18:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Chairman Sato! You have always been against this nonsense! Why did you suddenly change your mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.94,0:18:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,For so long you've been convincing us this is wrong, and now, all of a sudden, you start supporting it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.41,0:18:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not exactly the opposite, \Nso there's nothing to explain...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.95,0:18:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We may be a union, but the international economic laws are for everyone to obey, and we are no exception!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.19,0:18:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me... \NDid the company just bribe you to get out of their way!?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.25,0:18:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about? \NSome things are just good and some are not!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.38,0:19:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure the contents of this envelope\N will make quite a view for your eyes...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.21,0:19:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.85,0:19:06.23,top,,0,0,0,,Showa Labor Union chairman: \NThe spicy and colorful story of money, lust and abuse of authority!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.94,0:19:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn swindler!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.98,0:19:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't care less about what you think of me...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.81,0:19:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you don't cooperate, be prepared that tomorrow 50 000 people will enjoy this article.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.73,0:19:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone around will know about the scandal involving the labor union chairman, aspiring to be elected as the councilor.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.61,0:19:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you imagine how happy the paparazzi will be?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.08,0:19:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We are grateful to Taihei Company for all the efforts, but the further production expansion will be executed
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.02,0:19:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,according to the plan \Nprovided by the Goyo Business Committee.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.21,0:19:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.96,0:19:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you saying our plan was not sagacious enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.09,0:19:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,No, they both were equally effective. It's just...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.32,0:19:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Just what's the reason then?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.84,0:19:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Both plans involved \Nthe local subcontractor companies takeover.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.60,0:19:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, you both chose North Carolina for it. To give you the idea, how similar they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.29,0:19:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You found this manufacturer too...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.09,0:19:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The deciding factor was the cost.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.36,0:19:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The material base will be provided by the agricultural machinery factory, which is about to go bankrupt.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.52,0:19:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What the...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.44,0:20:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,This manufacturer will be stolen away right under our noses by another Japanese company!?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.37,0:20:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Getting in touch is all that matters.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.85,0:20:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the alternative plan was interesting too. Ms. Matsumoto from Taihei proposed a joint affair with subcontractors.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.35,0:20:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Our company found this plan quite remarkable as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.63,0:20:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, we wish to continue working with Taihei company, hoping for a productive cooperation in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.87,0:20:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather than hoping in the future, \Nwhy don't you right start now?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.89,0:20:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Ms. Matsumoto, I hope you don't mind that I read your report too. Have to say, this is indeed an outstanding work.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.64,0:20:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Showa is usually quite sluggish with the new ideas. \NBut with you in their staff, the company might change for good.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.65,0:20:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Gondo! Please restrain from insults here!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.19,0:20:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't mind me, I'm just thinking out loud.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.18,0:20:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,How should I know...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.40,0:20:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard that the new the factory owner is some Japanese.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.40,0:20:45.91,top,,0,0,0,,North Carolina, USA
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.31,0:20:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Seems like from now on we'll be manufacturing Japanese car parts here. That's definitely not something I saw coming of.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.43,0:20:50.41,top,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.29,0:20:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I also heard that even if you are in any way deficient, \Nthe owner will still hire you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.25,0:20:57.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But aren't Japanese managers \Ntreat their workers rather like slaves?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.15,0:20:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,If they try to, I'll enslave their company myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.31,0:21:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, in that case our union will intercede. \NThey will come up with something.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.83,0:21:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,If they underpay me a single cent, they'll be sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.18,0:21:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever is ahead, the Japanese are bound to see we don't do business here the way they are used to.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.32,0:21:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Although the manager and the boss were discarded, \Nwe still acquired a lot of valuable experience and information.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.65,0:21:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Go on, go on! \NThis evening we'll celebrate no matter what!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.32,0:21:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Ms. Yukie, there's nothing to celebrate. We just lost to the Goyo Committee and yielded them a perspective project.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.58,0:21:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And you aren't upset?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.91,0:21:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. This time they just were better.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.87,0:21:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But the fact that our cars are now being completely assembled outside of Japan is a general success.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.11,0:21:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it wonderful that people of different cultures,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.59,0:21:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,languages, and skin colors will now work together to create something wholesome for everyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.63,0:21:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If you put it that way...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.88,0:21:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,However, a few years later, when all Japanese manufacturers will switch their production to on-site manufacturing,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.08,0:21:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the supply will one day exceed demand and the market will suffer the cars oversupply. Ms. Sawako...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.10,0:21:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,When that happens, they will once again need your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.40,0:22:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Today I pray with all my heart that your business style \Nwould never change, no matter what!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.87,0:22:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,IMF - The International Monetary Fund
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.48,0:22:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,in the period between 1981 and 1984 has also placed some restrictions on exports from Japan to the United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.47,0:22:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Soon enough, cars produced on their continent became available to American buyers.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.48,0:22:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Over these four years, the price of all new cars in America has risen by 50% on average.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.34,0:22:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,If only the export self-restrictions weren't placed, the price increase would've hardly exceeded 27%.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.25,0:22:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result, buyers overpay for cars has reached an astronomical amount - more than $170 billion.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.73,0:22:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Converting this sum into yen at that time's exchange rate, \Nit's approximately 4 trillion yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.69,0:22:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, \Nthe buyers were overpaying one trillion yen per year.
